    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-07-09T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-07-09T05:00:00-05:00" n="192"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1271: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Chairman of the American Delegation (<persName
                            corresp="#p_GHS1" type="from">Gibson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                            >Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-09T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 9, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 9—4:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>318. In considering our 315 and 316 you will appreciate that the preliminary
                    draft of the resolution must be worked out in private conferences involving a
                    dozen or more delegations and eventually perhaps in public session. Hence we
                    will need room for negotiation. In view of this and of the urgency of the matter
                    we would appreciate it if you could give us any general views on the <persName
                        corresp="#p_SSJ1">Simon</persName> draft and on our comment by tomorrow
                    Sunday and we will keep you advised as important drafting changes are worked out
                    here. We shall be continuing discussions with the British today regarding the
                    resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GHS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
